modules.description: This module provides benchmarking operations for arithmetic (addition, multiplication, squaring, doubling) and cryptographic checks (equality, negation, inversion) on elements of a mathematical field. It works with pregenerated field elements (zero, one, random values) and byte representations for serialization, targeting use cases in cryptographic protocol development and performance analysis of field-based computations.

This module implements benchmarking routines for arithmetic and cryptographic operations on mathematical field elements, including addition, multiplication, equality checks, and inversion. It operates on field elements like zero, one, and random values, along with their byte representations for serialization. It is used to measure performance in cryptographic protocol development and optimize field-based computations.
